                                                                  7529 1451
  General methodology: The global approach considered in this     7529 1451
          work is presented in the following paper: Modern        7529 1451
          nuclear data evaluation with the TALYS code system,     7529 1451
          A.J. Koning and D. Rochman, Nuclear Data Sheets 113     7529 1451
          (2012) 2841.                                            7529 1451
                                                                  7529 1451
  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           7529 1451
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         7529 1451
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR7529 1451
       expands from 0 to 1.301283E+2 eV. A total of               7529 1451
       2 l-values are used and 200 resonances. The resonance      7529 1451
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              7529 1451
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       7529 1451
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          7529 1451
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     7529 1451
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    7529 1451
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  7529 1451
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   7529 1451
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          7529 1451
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       7529 1451
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    7529 1451
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       7529 1451
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         7529 1451
       The s-wave average level spacing is 0.801 eV and           7529 1451
       the s-wave neutron strength is 0.0002109 1e-4.             7529 1451
                                                                  7529 1451
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  7529 1451
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    7529 1451
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    7529 1451
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   7529 1451
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    7529 1451
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              7529 1451
